Hi,

we've just released another minor release of bzr-gtk, 0.91.0. This
release fixes some bugs, and adds a couple more UI bits and is intended
to be compatible with Bazaar 0.91.

The changes since 0.90.0 are:

 UI

  * Added keyboard shortcuts for closing windows and exiting Olive.
    (#139559, Daniel Schierbeck)

  * The tip revision will be automatically selected in the branch
visualization
    window. (#144244, Daniel Schierbeck)

  * Updated olive-gtk.desktop: Polish translation and additional categories.
    (Mateusz Korniak)

 BUG FIXES

  * Fix the "Complete Diff" entry in DiffWindow to show the whole diff.
    (#140512, James Westby)

  * Right-clicking in Olive's file list works again. (#136310, Mark Lee)

  * Annotate context menu works again. (Daniel Schierbeck)

  * Fixed push (with overwite) behavior when branches are diverged.
    (Mateusz Korniak)

  * Local missing revisions are remote extra revisions (Missing
revisions menu
    item in Olive). (Mateusz Korniak)

 INTERNALS

  * `bzr viz --limit` much more faster than before. (John Arbash Meinel)

  * Use get_apparent_author, rename variables to 'author'. (Aaron Bentley)

  * Added default_branch_path to MergeDialog and use it from olive-gtk.
    (Mateusz Korniak)

This release can be downloaded from:

 * https://launchpad.net/bzr-gtk/0.91/0.91.0/+download/bzr-gtk-0.91.0.tar.gz
(mirror: http://phanatic.hu/bzr-gtk/bzr-gtk-0.91.0.tar.gz)

The tarball (the .tar.gz) has been signed with my GPG key (F1D076A3).
The signature can be downloaded from
http://phanatic.hu/bzr-gtk/bzr-gtk-0.91.0.tar.gz.asc. To verify the
tarball, run:

$ gpg --verify bzr-gtk-0.91.0.tar.gz.asc

Bugs and requests for new features can be reported on launchpad,
https://bugs.launchpad.net/bzr-gtk.

The upcoming 0.92.0 release already has some prospective features, like
making `bzr viz` 5x faster on bzr.dev.

You may notice that the changelog features a bunch of new names. That's
a really great thing that we have so many contributors. On the other
hand the project maintenance became a bit difficult for us. So we
decided to create a bzr-gtk mailing list, and thanks to Jelmer, Martin,
and the Canonical sysadmins, it's already available:

https://lists.canonical.com/mailman/listinfo/bzr-gtk

We also plan to track merge requests, a Budle Buggy instance will be set
up in a few days, thanks to Jelmer.

Another change you may have noticed is that I'm rolling this release
(and probably the following ones as well). Please bear with me, this is
my first time ever :)

Enjoy!

Cheers,
