We're pleased to announce the 3.0.0 release of Breezy.

Breezy is a version control system implemented in Python with support
for multiple repository formats including git, and an emphasis on
hackability.

The project is a fork of the dormant Bazaar project, and this release is a
culmination of about a year worth of work since the fork. Key changes
=66rom the last release of Bazaar:

* Compatibility with Python 3 (and Python 2.7 still)
* Support for Git repositories
* Built-in support for extra commands previously provided by plugins,
  most notably: grep, fastimport/fastexport, bisect, upload, stats, heads
* ~100 smaller bug fixes (https://launchpad.net/brz/+milestone/3.0.0)

For a fuller (but still incomplete) list of changes, see our changelog
at https://code.breezy-vcs.org/breezy/trunk/view/head:/doc/en/release-notes=
/brz-3.0.txt.

Installation
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D

You can install Breezy 3.0.0:

* From source, by downloading the tarball from https://launchpad.net/brz/3.=
0/3.0.0/+download/breezy-3.0.0.tar.gz (GPG signature at https://launchpad.n=
et/brz/3.0/3.0.0/+download/breezy-3.0.0.tar.gz.asc)
* From pip by running "pip install breezy"
* If you're running Debian, straight from Debian unstable
  (https://packages.debian.org/sid/brz) or testing
  (https://packages.debian.org/testing/brz)
* If you're running Ubuntu, you can install Bionic and Cosmic packages
  from the PPA at https://launchpad.net/~brz/+archive/ubuntu/daily
* If you're running FreeBSD, there is a port (see https://www.freshports.or=
g/devel/brz) available.

Upgrading from Bazaar
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D

The Breezy configuration lives in ``~/.config/breezy``, but it will read
``~/.bazaar`` if the former does not exist. Since the API for Breezy is dif=
ferent
than that of Bazaar, any existing plugins will need to be ported manually.
Plugins you have installed in ``~/.bazaar/plugins`` will almost certainly n=
ot
load.

Breezy has dropped support for the FTP transport.

The command line tool is named ``brz`` rather than ``bzr`` but can be alias=
ed for
compatibility.

Supported plugins
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

Several of the plugins that were available for Bazaar and that were not mer=
ged into Breezy itself have been ported to work with Breezy.

* breezy-debian (based on bzr-builddeb)
* brz-builder (based on bzr-builder)
* brz-loom (based on bzr-loom)
* loggerhead
* qbrz (based on qbzr)

Feedback
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D

Please report any bugs on Launchpad (https://bugs.launchpad.net/brz/+filebu=
g).

You can also reach us here on the Bazaar mailing list and on the #bzr IRC c=
hannel on Freenode <https://www.freenode.net/.

 -- Martin, Vincent and Jelmer

